-- SunPower Restructuring Cost May More Than Double to $40 Million
-- B y   W i l l   W a d e
-- 2013-01-11T21:53:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-11/sunpower-restructuring-cost-may-more-than-double-to-40-million.html
SunPower Corp. (SPWR) , the solar
manufacturer that’s majority-owned by  Total SA (FP) , expects to
record a charge of $33 million to $40 million for a
restructuring announced in October.  The “majority” of the charge will be recorded in the
fourth quarter, San Jose, California-based SunPower said in a
filing today. The company had earlier said it would take a
charge of $10 million to $17 million for the restructuring
program.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Will Wade at 
 wwade4@bloomberg.net  